            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><hr />\n<h2 id=\"summary-key-insights\">Summary: Key Insights</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">This analysis reveals several patterns in the National Gallery of Art collection:</span>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Finding</th>\n<th>Significance</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Peak production in 17th-19th centuries</strong></td>\n<td>Aligns with European art historical canon</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>American artists well-represented</strong></td>\n<td>NGA's mission emphasizes American art</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Oil on canvas dominates</strong></td>\n<td>Traditional Western painting medium</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Some artists represented by 100+ works</strong></td>\n<td>Deep holdings allow comprehensive study</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"technical-implementation-notes\">Technical Implementation Notes</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Data Source</strong>: <a href=\"https://github.com/NationalGalleryOfArt/opendata\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">National Gallery of Art Open Data</a></li>\n<li><strong>Visualization Principles</strong>: Edward Tufte's <em>The Visual Display of Quantitative Information</em></li>\n<li><strong>Toolchain</strong>: marimo + pandas + matplotlib</li>\n<li><strong>Collaboration</strong>: This notebook supports <a href=\"https://github.com/marimo-team/marimo-pair\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">marimo-pair</a> for real-time editing</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><em>Generated: 2026-04-17 00:12</em></span></span>"
